Senegal Plans to Use $200 Million Sukuk Proceeds for Budgetary Support

-- B y   D r e w   H i n s h a w
-- 
2011-06-15T10:28:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/senegal-plans-to-use-200-million-sukuk-proceeds-for-budgetary-support.html
Senegal intends to use the proceeds
of a $200 million sukuk sale planned for later this year for
budgetary support, Abdoulaye Diop, the country’s finance
minister, told a conference in Dakar, the country’s capital,
today.  Senegal wants to diversify its funding sources to attract
money from Islamic countries, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Hinshaw in Dakar at 
 dhinshaw@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  